comment.text:
Because MemberInfo.GetCustomAttributes works different to Attribute.GetCustomAttributes, using the static IsDefined on Attribute will yield the correct results for a PropertyInfo when using the inherit flag.

Just change this line in your test with the one following and it passes:
Assert.IsTrue(nameProperty.IsDefined(typeof(InheritableAttribute), false));
Assert.IsTrue(Attribute.IsDefined(nameProperty, typeof(InheritableAttribute), true));

See this blog post for more details:
http://blogs.msdn.com/weitao/archive/2009/05/28/override-properties-ii-getcustomattributes.aspx for more details.
